deck: Vengeful ghost from a japanese urban legend.
description:
Fables

Kuchisake-onna, the slit-mouthed woman from Japanese urban legends, appears in the Fairest story arc The Hidden Kingdom. Her real name is Mayumi. Before the Adversary's invasion, she was a member of the Heika's court in the Fable Homeland of the Hidden Kingdom. Unbeknown to her, the Seii Taishogun was secretly laying the way for the invasion and planned to become the new ruler of the Hidden Kingdom. He offered to make her Mayumi his Empress, but she rejected him and called him "a parasite on the court". He responded by slitting Mayumi's cheeks in anger. Unable to live with her face mutilated like that, she committed seppuku (a form of Japanese ritual suicide by disembowelment) - "or someone faked it". Her ghost began lurking in the washrooms and corridors of the Heika's palace, haunting mirrors. Eventually, she managed to take on a physical form and escaped the Homelands with a group of yokai who had been banished from the court. The group started a new life in a hidden Fable community in Tokyo. Centuries later, she has become the enforcer of Tomoko, a powerful female kitsune who is a Yakuza leader. Mayumi wears a surgical mask to hide the disfigurement. She enjoys scaring people by asking them, "Am I beautiful?", before removing the mask and asking "How about now?". Eventually, with the help of Rapunzel, the fugitives manage to find their way back to their homeland via a magical portal.

deck: The father of Princess Painting.
description:
Origin

Painting King is the ruler of the Kingdom of Painting and father of the Princess Painting. His daughter posts a Quest request on a Questing board which is subsequently picked up by Finn the Human and Jake the Dog who require some urgent questing. When they arrive at the Painting Castle they are greeted by the Painting King who fields their questions regarding his daughters kidnapping. Painting King is confused and calls down his daughter informing Jake and Finn she is right there. Painting Princess clarifies to Finn and Jake informing them that they took a notice from the back of the Questing Board which means its in reverse and that they need to make the Monkey Wizard kidnap her.

Creation

Painting King is a Boom! Studioes published character created by writers Paul Tobin, Colleen Coover and artist Wook Jin Clark. Painting King first appears in Adventure Time: The Flip Side.

Powers and Abilities

Painting King is the king and ruler of the Painting Kingdom. Painting King's head is a canvas that continuously changes and displays various painted portraits in all manner of different painting styles, themes and homages to famous paintings.

deck: The daughter of the Painting King.
description:
Origin

Princess Painting is the daughter of Painting King and is the princess of the Kingdom of Painting. She posts a Quest request explaining that she has been kidnapped by a Monkey Wizard on the reverse side of a Questing board which is subsequently picked up by Finn the Human and Jake the Dog who require some urgent questing. When they arrive at the Painting Castle they are greeted by the Painting King who fields their questions regarding his daughters kidnapping. Painting King is confused and calls down his daughter informing Jake and Finn she is right there. Painting Princess clarifies to Finn and Jake informing them that they took a notice from the back of the Questing Board which means its in reverse and that they need to make the Monkey Wizard kidnap her.

They are also warmed that if they fail to accomplish this that Ooo would be doomed.

Creation

deck: Sharpshooter is a psiot and a member of the mercenary team The Specialists.

Origin

Sharpshooter is a psiot with visual hyper acuity linked to heightened mental processing power - she knows what her opponents are going to do before they do it. She was recruited by Simon Oreck as part of his Specialists team to replace the original H.A.R.D. Corps. Sharpshooter is in a long term relationship with team mate Big Boy.
name: Sharpshooter

deck: Big Boy is a psiot and a member of the mercenary team The Specialists.
description:
Origin

Big Boy is a psiot whose brain generates polypeptides, amino acids and other growth hormones to build massive amounts of muscle. He is kept alive by insulin pumps and cybertech without which he'd die of cancer, diabetes or his body ripping itself apart. Big Boy was recruited by Simon Oreck as part of his Specialists team to replace the original H.A.R.D. Corps. Big Boy is in a long term relationship with team mate Sharpshooter.
name: Big Boy
